// =============================================================================
// core/database/sqlite/native/triggers/mod.vr
// =============================================================================
// Layer: 5 (parsing) / 6 (storage) / 4 (firing)
// Spec: sqlite-native.md §17.1
//
// Trigger catalogue. The L5 parser builds `TriggerDef` records that
// the L6 SchemaCache stores; the L4 interpreter fires them via
// `Gosub trigger_id` at the appropriate DML hook (BEFORE / AFTER /
// INSTEAD-OF). Each trigger compiles to a sub-program in the
// VdbeProgram constant pool.
//
// This module is the data-layer source of truth — the AST/codegen
// path will route through it once the SCreateTrigger AST node lands
// in `l5_sql/ast.vr`. Until then, the catalogue is exercisable
// directly from L7 API as `Connection.add_trigger(spec)`.
// =============================================================================

module core.database.sqlite.native.triggers;

public module spec;
public module store;
public module fire;
